1 2. An age less than thirty-five (35) years old and was Been
2 manufactured for use in either the United States Armed Forces or any
3 country that was a member of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
4 at the time the vehicle was manufactured. Such vehicle shall have
5 been subsequently authorized for sale to civilians, except that
6 military surplus vehicle does not include a tracked vehicle;
7 3. For each occupant, safety belts or safety shoulder harnesses
8 which shall be installed pursuant to 49 C.F.R., Section 571.208 et
9 seq.; and
10 4. Equipment required by the provisions of Sections 12-201
11 through 12-232 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title, with
12 respect to equipment on vehicles.
13 B. A Beginning November 1, 2025, any military surplus vehicle
14 operated on the streets and highways of this state shall be
15 registered as a motor vehicle.
16 C. Military surplus vehicles may be used as other vehicles of
17 the same type, except military surplus vehicles may not transport
18 people for hire.
19 D. Military surplus vehicles that were not able to be tagged
20 because of the 35-year clause may not be fined.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
